content:
Messages on the Logs page in the Salesforce Backup managed package are simpler, easier to scan, and more informative. The Log Name column now shows only when jobs have started and complete. New job status categories group issues based on severity: errors that require the help of Salesforce Customer Support, alerts about states—such as missing permissions—that you can fix, and informational messages that don't require action. We also improved some object status codes for clarity and accuracy.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited editions.

How: In the Salesforce Backup managed package, select the Logs tab. You can review more informative object status codes on a log's detail page. For example, objects that were previously marked as NOT_VISIBLE are now marked as MISSING_PERMISSIONS, helping you understand the next steps you can take to fix the issue.
title: Improved Salesforce Backup Logs for Lightning Experience
